column1: Why were the strawberries sad? because their mother was in a jam!
column3: Jam can refer to a fruit preserve (first meaning) or a situation of being stuck (second meaning).
column4: The chef made a delicious strawberry jam for the dessert.
column5: The car got stuck in a traffic jam during rush hour.

column1: You know youre drunk when the cat barks.
column3: Bark can refer to the sound a dog makes (first meaning) or the outer covering of a tree (second meaning).
column4: The dog started to bark loudly as the mailman approached the house.
column5: The trees bark was rough and weathered from years of exposure to the elements.

column1: Why did the chicken fall into the well? he couldnt see that well.
column3: Well can refer to a water source (first meaning) or a state of being good (second meaning).
column4: The village relies on the old well for drinking water.
column5: She was feeling well after recovering from her illness.
